        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-08-12 10:05:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOk, thankyou! this is my understanding from both `movingVidCertificates` commits -\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/oom/+/92888 and this:\n\n1) Effective certs are resources, part of OOM.\n2) Any file in this OOM resources/certs/* will eventually end as secret, mounted on the instance in /opt/app/vid/etc/*.\n3) Now no need to add the certificates into the docker-image, thus /opt/app/vid/etc should *always* be mounted. (vid will fail to start if not)\n\nIf I'm getting, I suggest two further commits (possibly after these are merged):\n1) Instead of /opt/app/vid/etc/, use /opt/app/vid/etc/certs (or similar).\n2) Document the new \"required\" volume mapping in `installation.rst`.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
